	<LINE>[These Rates differ little from the usual Non-participating Premiums.]</LINE>
	<LINE>* Thus a person of 30 may secure £1000 at death by a yearly payment,</LINE>
	<LINE>during life, of £20 15s., which would generally secure elsewhere about £800</LINE>
	<LINE>only. Or, he may secure £1000 by 21 yearly payments of £27 13s. 4d., being-</LINE>
	<LINE>free of payment after 50.</LINE>
	<LINE>t At age 40 the Premium ceasing at age 60 is, for £1000, £33 14s. 2d. ;</LINE>
	<LINE>being about the same as is usually charged during the whole term of life.</LINE>
	<LINE>Before the Premiums have ceased the Policy will have shared in at least</LINE>
	<LINE>one Division of Profits. To Professional Men and others, whose income is</LINE>
	<LINE>dependent on continuance of health, the limited payment system is specially</LINE>
	<LINE>recommended.</LINE>
